# Pre-push capability matrix for Linux/aarch64 -- the primary LP64 dev target.
# Consumed by tests/check/run.sh (via `make check`).
#
# Columns:  CHECK  CELL  STATUS  [NOTE...]
#   CHECK : build | test | doc
#   STATUS: require -> must pass; a FAIL fails the gate (nonzero exit)
#           skip    -> not applicable on this platform; printed with reason, never run
#           todo    -> wanted but not yet wired/trusted; printed, never gates
#
# CELL grammar:
#   build  <conf>[/release]              conf = emu | emu-g | emu-wrt
#                                        /release = link with DISPTRCHECK off
#   test   cunit                         dual-ABI C library unit tests
#   test   {lp64,web}/<conf>/<runmode>   runmode = interp | jit | jitB
#   test   jitperf                       self-contained c0/c1/c1B bench + bit-equiv
#   doc    <name>
#
# The matrix is identical across platforms; what differs per platform is the
# STATUS (the *trust*).  Keeping skip/todo cells listed (not deleted) is the
# point: untested surface stays visible instead of silently rotting.

# ---- build matrix ----
build  emu                require
build  emu-g              require    headless build the lp64/web suites run under
build  emu/release        require    release link-check: DISPTRCHECK off must still build
build  emu-wrt            todo       wince/wrt config unmaintained

# ---- test matrix ----
test   cunit              require
test   lp64/emu-g/interp  require
test   lp64/emu-g/jit     require    aarch64 Dis JIT is trusted
test   web/emu-g/interp   require
test   jitperf            require    also a JIT bit-identity correctness gate
test   kernel             require    native-kernel e2e under qemu -M virt (tests/kernel, ~4 min)

# ---- docs (scoped, not yet wired) ----
doc    man-coverage       todo       every /dis cmd has a man/1 page; then per-flag usage
